com.facetec.sdk

Class FaceTecCustomization

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facetec.sdk.FaceTecCustomization

  • public final class FaceTecCustomization
extends java.lang.Object
    Class used to customize the look and feel of the FaceTec interface. FaceTec SDK ships with a default theme but has a variety of variables that you can use to configure to your application's needs.
    To customize the User Interface, simply create an instance of FaceTecCustomization and set some, or all, of the variables.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int activityThemeId 
      int exitAnimationSuccessResourceID
      Set this variable to a R.anim file to customize the transition out animation for a successful session.
      Default is -1.
      int exitAnimationUnsuccessResourceID
      Set this variable to a R.anim file to customize the transition out animation for an unsuccessful session.
      Setting this to 0 will disable the animation.
      Default is -1.
      static java.lang.String overrideResultScreenSuccessMessage
      This function allows special runtime control of the success message shown when the success animation occurs.
      Please note that you can also customize this string via the standard customization/localization methods provided.
      Special runtime access is enabled for this text because the developer may wish to change this text depending on the mode of operation.
      Default is "Success".
      FaceTecSecurityWatermarkImage securityWatermarkImage
      Customize the FaceTec Security Watermark Image by selecting from 1 of the 3 available FaceTec watermarks.
